1 (iii) If a motion picture is produced and available to motion picture
2 houses with open movie captioning, a place of public accommodation that controls, operates,
3 owns, or leases a motion picture house with [eight] FOUR or more screens in the State shall
4 provide open movie captioning for at least two screenings for each motion picture it screens
5 each week.
6 (iv) Beginning 3 weeks after a motion picture premieres, a place of
7 accommodation that controls, operates, owns, or leases a motion picture house with [eight]
8 FOUR or more screens in the State may provide open movie captioning with reasonable
9 notice.
10 (D) ON OR BEFORE THE 10TH DAY OF THE MONTH, EACH MONTH, A MOTION
11 PICTURE HOUSE THAT IS A PLACE OF PUBLIC ACCOMMODATION SHALL REPORT TO
